<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFB2FFE8FF1CFD1B48A7FB55" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB2FFE8FF1CFD1B4BF2FC95" blockId="3.[113,765,716,1188]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FF1CFD1B498BFD15" box="[151,233,717,740]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Notes. –</emphasis>
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB2FFE8FE31FD1A4BF4FD15" box="[442,662,716,740]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Adiantum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lunulatum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FE31FD1A4BF4FD15" box="[442,662,716,740]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Adiantum lunulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
included references to plates from 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB2FFE8FEF0FD3B4B7AFCF5" author="PETIVER" box="[379,536,748,772]" firstAuthor="PETIVER" journalOrPublisher="London" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" refId="ref10041" refString="PETIVER J. (1702 - 1709). Gazophylaciis naturae &amp; artis decades. London." title="Gazophylaciis naturae &amp; artis decades" type="book" year="1702">PETIVER (1702</bibRefCitation>
– 1709)’s 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FDF3FD3A49A1FCD5" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Gazophylacii Naturae</emphasis>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB2FFE8FF7EFCDB48E8FCD5" author="RHEEDE" box="[245,394,780,804]" firstAuthor="RHEEDE" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" refId="ref10115" refString="RHEEDE [TOT DRAAKESTEIN], H. A. VAN (1678 - 1693). Hortus Indicus Malabaricus. 12 vol. Amsterdam. [vol. 12, 1693]" title="Hortus Indicus Malabaricus" type="book" year="1678">RHEEDE (1678</bibRefCitation>
– 1693)’s 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FE6DFCDB4B95FCD5" box="[486,759,780,804]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Hortus Indicus Malabaricus</emphasis>
, as well to a specimen (or possibly more) received from Malabar or 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFB2FFE8FF04FC9B49D8FC95" box="[143,186,845,868]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Java</collectingRegion>
(“ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FF58FC9A4B15FC95" box="[211,631,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">
<location id="D437604FFFB2FFE8FF58FC9A48C8FC95" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:59418782FFB2FFE8FFFAFE2148A7FB55:D437604FFFB2FFE8FF58FC9A48C8FC95" box="[211,426,844,868]" name="Habitat in Malabara" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" stateProvince="Jawa Timur">Habitat in Malabara</location>
&amp; 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFB2FFE8FE46FC9B489DFC95" box="[461,511,845,868]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Java</collectingRegion>
, unde missa
</emphasis>
”).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB2FFE8FF1CFCBB48B6FB95" blockId="3.[113,765,716,1188]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB2FFE8FF1CFCBB48E6FC75" author="MERRILL" box="[151,388,876,900]" firstAuthor="MERRILL" journalOrPublisher="Philippine J. Sci." page="334" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" pagination="329 - 388" part="19" refId="ref9969" refString="MERRILL, E. D. (1921). A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica. Philippine J. Sci. 19: 329 - 388." title="A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica" type="journal article" year="1921">MERRILL (1921: 334)</bibRefCitation>
stated that: “the actual 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFB2FFE8FD12FCBB4BABFC74" box="[665,713,877,901]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">type</typeStatus>
was apparently a Javan specimen, the Malabar reference being apparently added either from Avenka Rheede 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FDD4FC7B4B9EFC35" box="[607,764,940,964]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Hort. Malabar.</emphasis>
12: 72, tab. 40, or from Petiver 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FE49FC1B4894FC15" box="[450,502,973,996]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Gaz.</emphasis>
tab. 54, f. 10, both cited as representing the species”. As a single specimen of original material (from unknown origin but bearing references to both plates) is present in G-PREL [
<specimenCode id="814E9EEFFFB2FFE8FE39FBFA4B59FBB5" box="[434,571,1068,1092]" collectionCode="G" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" type="Herbarium">G00800009</specimenCode>
], Merrill’s implicit lectotypification is accepted here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB2FFE8FF1CFBBA48A7FB55" blockId="3.[113,765,716,1188]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">
This was overlooked by 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB2FFE8FE1AFBBA4B09FB75" author="MORTON" box="[401,619,1132,1156]" firstAuthor="MORTON" journalOrPublisher="Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb." page="370" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" pagination="283 - 396" part="38" refId="ref10010" refString="MORTON, C. V. (1974). William Roxburgh's fern types. Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb. 38: 283 - 396." title="William Roxburgh's fern types" type="journal article" year="1974">MORTON (1974: 370)</bibRefCitation>
, who selected the same specimen as 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFB2FFE8FED6FB5A48A3FB55" box="[349,449,1164,1188]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
